<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>When the Fed conducts contractionary monetary policy, what happens to bond prices?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Rise due to lower interest rates</option>
            <option letter="b">Fall due to higher interest rates</option>
            <option letter="c">Remain unchanged</option>
            <option letter="d">Cannot be determined</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Contractionary monetary policy raises interest rates, causing bond prices to fall because bond prices and interest rates are inversely related.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>The long-run aggregate supply curve is vertical because:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Prices are sticky</option>
            <option letter="b">Wages are flexible</option>
            <option letter="c">Output is determined by factor inputs and technology</option>
            <option letter="d">The money supply is constant</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>LRAS is vertical because long-run output is determined by the economy's productive capacity (labor, capital, and technology), not the price level.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>An increase in government spending financed by borrowing will:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Decrease interest rates</option>
            <option letter="b">Increase private investment</option>
            <option letter="c">Increase interest rates</option>
            <option letter="d">Have no effect on interest rates</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>Government borrowing increases demand for loanable funds, pushing up interest rates and potentially crowding out private investment.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>The real exchange rate appreciates when:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Domestic inflation is higher than foreign inflation</option>
            <option letter="b">Domestic inflation is lower than foreign inflation</option>
            <option letter="c">The nominal exchange rate depreciates</option>
            <option letter="d">The trade deficit increases</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The real exchange rate appreciates when domestic inflation is lower than foreign inflation, making domestic goods relatively less expensive.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
